{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17638830","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17638830"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:59:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:59:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17739"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17739","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17739"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.86,0,0.05,0.09,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10453"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75827"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10453","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10453"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17739"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61340"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"688"},{"type":"tags","id":"1109"},{"type":"tags","id":"1307"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4487"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10113"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24406"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24407"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75827","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75827"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 55-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-month history of fatigue and weakness. He reports weight gain despite a stable diet, hoarseness, dry skin, cold intolerance, shortness of breath on exertion, constipation, decreased hearing, and swelling in his legs. He has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, vital signs were within normal limits. There is noticeable periorbital puffiness and non-pitting oedema in the lower extremities. His skin is dry and cool to touch.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely underlying condition?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hypothyroidism","Chronic kidney disease","Congestive heart failure","Cushing\u0027s syndrome","Depression"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with a constellation of symptoms that are classic for \u003Cstrong\u003Ehypothyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E. These include fatigue, weight gain, dry skin, cold intolerance, and constipation. The presence of hoarseness, decreased hearing, and non-pitting oedema further supports this diagnosis, as these can be associated with myxedema, a feature of severe hypothyroidism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic kidney disease\u003C/strong\u003E could cause fatigue and oedema, but it would not cause cold intolerance, dry skin, or hoarseness.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECongestive heart failure\u003C/strong\u003E causes dyspnoea on exertion but oedema will be pitting and it would not explain the dry skin, cold intolerance, or constipation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECushing\u0027s syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by weight gain and fatigue, but other features; central obesity, moon face, and skin changes like striae are not described here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDepression\u003C/strong\u003E can cause fatigue and weight changes, but it would not account for the physical signs such as dry skin, hoarseness, or oedema.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Hypothyroidism can present with a wide range of symptoms including fatigue, weight gain, dry skin, and cold intolerance.","The diagnosis of hypothyroidism is often clinical, supported by laboratory tests showing elevated TSH and low free T4 levels.","Common symptoms of hypothyroidism can overlap with other conditions, making clinical evaluation crucial."],"references":["Chaker L, Bianco AC, Jonklaas J, Peeters RP. Hypothyroidism. Lancet. 2017 Sep 23;390(10101):1550-1562. doi: 10.1016/S0140-6736(17)30703-1. Epub 2017 Mar 20. PMID: 28336049; PMCID: PMC6619426.","Zamwar UM, Muneshwar KN. Epidemiology, Types, Causes, Clinical Presentation, Diagnosis, and Treatment of Hypothyroidism. Cureus. 2023 Sep 30;15(9):e46241. doi: 10.7759/cureus.46241. PMID: 37908940; PMCID: PMC10613832.","Wilson SA, Stem LA, Bruehlman RD. Hypothyroidism: Diagnosis and Treatment. Am Fam Physician. 2021 May 15;103(10):605-613. PMID: 33983002."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61340"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17739"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61340","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61340"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-31T21:11:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-31T21:11:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10453"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75827"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name